        {
          "name": "task_contract_driver",
          "receiver": "&self",
          "params": [
            { "name": "items_dir", "ty": "std::path::PathBuf" }
          ],
          "returns": "cli_driver::task_contract::TaskContractDriver",
          "is_async": false,
          "generics": [],
          "has_default_impl": false,
          "where_predicates": [],
          "docs": "Construct a fully-wired TaskContractDriver for the requested items_dir. Wires FsTaskContractReader, FsImplCatalogSignalReader, and FsImplPlanReader into a PreReviewGateInteractor (check service, D7: three-port constructor) and CoverageVerifyInteractor (coverage service, two-port constructor). Wraps both as Arc<dyn PreReviewGateService> and Arc<dyn CoverageVerifyService> and injects them into TaskContractDriver::new."
        },
        {
          "name": "task_contract_check",
          "receiver": "&self",
          "params": [
            { "name": "layer", "ty": "Option<String>" },
            { "name": "track_id", "ty": "String" },
            { "name": "items_dir", "ty": "std::path::PathBuf" }
          ],
          "returns": "Result<cli_driver::CommandOutcome, CompositionError>",
          "is_async": false,
          "generics": [],
          "has_default_impl": false,
          "where_predicates": [],
          "docs": "Wire and invoke the pre-review liveness gate check. Constructs a TaskContractDriver via task_contract_driver(items_dir), then dispatches TaskContractInput::Check { layer, track_id }. The driver parses CLI strings, calls the check use case (filtered by impl-plan.json task statuses per D7), and renders Passed/Blocked outcomes as CommandOutcome. When layer is None, iterates all 6 canonical TDDD layers and returns a combined verdict."
        },
        {
          "name": "task_contract_coverage",
          "receiver": "&self",
          "params": [
            { "name": "track_id", "ty": "String" },
            { "name": "items_dir", "ty": "std::path::PathBuf" }
          ],
          "returns": "Result<cli_driver::CommandOutcome, CompositionError>",
          "is_async": false,
          "generics": [],
          "has_default_impl": false,
          "where_predicates": [],
          "docs": "Wire and invoke the attribution-completeness coverage check. Constructs a TaskContractDriver via task_contract_driver(items_dir), then dispatches TaskContractInput::Coverage { track_id }. The driver calls the coverage use case and renders Passed/Blocked outcomes as CommandOutcome. Coverage checks all 6 canonical TDDD layers (whole-catalogue invariant)."
        }
      ],
      "module_path": "task_contract",
      "docs": "Composition root for the task-contract command family. Wires FsTaskContractReader, FsImplCatalogSignalReader, FsImplPlanReader (D7), PreReviewGateInteractor, CoverageVerifyInteractor, and TaskContractDriver for both sotp task-contract check and sotp task-contract coverage subcommands.",
